Nightmare Mudlib SimulEfun: reflexive()

string reflexive(string|object);

DESCRIPTION
Returns the appropriate reflexive pronoun for a given gender.
If you pass a gender string, it returns a value for that gender.
If you pass an object, then it returns the appropriate reflexive
pronoun based on that object's gender.

EXAMPLES
reflexive(find_player("lassondra")) returns "herself"
reflexive("neuter") returns "itself"

LOCATION
/secure/SimulEfun/english.c

SEE ALSO
nominative(), objective(), possessive()
